<div class="text">
    <p>
        Figure 9 shows the annual variability for 20CR predictors, and G-20CR for five tide gauges from the Arctic, Antarctica, Australia, New Zealand, and the northwest coast of US. Our analysis has shown that tide gauges in these regions show relatively higher drop in the variability of the predictor variables and reconstructed surges as the they go back in time compared to the recent time (Figure 1 &9). G-E20C (not shown here) also shows such a decrease in annual variability in some of these tide gauges. Some of the tide gauges like Base Prat and Kerguelen show a very rapid decline in the variability time series leading to a changepoint year in the 2000s. Therefore, these tide gauges and others with similar erroneous behavior are not considered for further analysis (i.e. trend analysis). They are marked in red in Figure 2 and Figure 3. 
    </p>
